cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with speech recognition, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper deals with speech signals and their phonetic structures. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses machine learning techniques such as Audio Word2Vec and autoencoder to learn the phonetic structures of spoken and text words. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses AI techniques to develop an almost unsupervised speech recognition system. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Although the paper does not deal with computer vision, some of the techniques used in the paper such as embeddings and autoencoder are also used in computer vision.
